snippet: Dozens of problematic ballots could determine the fate of an initiative that seeks to establish a $15 minimum wage for many workers in the airport city of SeaTac.
abstract: Dozens of problematic ballots could determine fate of initiative seeking to establish $15 minimum wage for many workers in SeaTac, Wash; both labor and business groups spent large sums to influence outcome.
lead_paragraph: Dozens of problematic ballots could determine the fate of an initiative that seeks to establish a $15 minimum wage for many workers in the airport city of SeaTac.

headline.main: Washington: Minimum Wage Outcome Is Uncertain
